An Igbosere High Court in Lagos State yesterday ordered a Senior Advocate of Nigeria (SAN), Rickey Tarfa, to present a fresh medical report explaining his health condition. Justice Adedayo Akintoye gave the order following the application of Tarfa, who is standing trial on a 26-count charge of offering gratification to two judges of the Federal High Court – Justices Hyeladzira Nganjiwa and Mohammed Yunusa, for more time to recuperate from a surgery. The charges include alleged perversion of the course of justice, but he, however, pleaded not guilty to and was granted bail on self-recognition. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that the case has been stalled since Jan. 21, after the defendant travelled abroad for medical treatment. When the case came up on March 11, March 19 and May 8 after he returned from his trip abroad, the defendant was unable to enter the courtroom as he stayed downstairs in his car. According to his counsel, Mr Jelili Owonikoko (SAN), Tarfa was unable to climb the staircase leading to Akintoye’s courtroom, even on a wheelchair, because of the severity of his ill-health